<refsect1 id="GladePlaceholder.description" role="desc">
<title role="desc.title">Description</title>
<para>
Generally in Glade, container widgets are implemented with <link linkend="GladePlaceholder"><type>GladePlaceholder</type></link> 
children to allow users to 'click' and add thier widgets to a container. 
It is the responsability of the plugin writer to create placeholders for 
container widgets where appropriate; usually in <link linkend="GladePostCreateFunc"><type>GladePostCreateFunc</type></link> 
when the <link linkend="GladeCreateReason"><type>GladeCreateReason</type></link> is <link linkend="GLADE-CREATE-USER:CAPS"><literal>GLADE_CREATE_USER</literal></link>.</para>
<para>

</para>
</refsect1>

